        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 5:46PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
east of Gerty, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Mcalester Regional Airport...
Pittsburg...                      Kiowa...
Krebs...                          Haywood...
Blanco...                         Ashland...
Savanna...                        Alderson...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
